  <main>
    
<section class='container'>
  <h2 class='section-title'>Request a technical discussion</h2>
  <p class='section-intro'>Use this page as the front door for serious technical conversations. It is better to ask a few structured questions than to let generic enquiries create noise.</p>
  <div class='grid-2'>
    <div class='card'>
      <h3>Recommended inputs</h3>
      <ul class='clean'>
        <li>Rotor model and manufacturer</li>
        <li>Target pressure or rpm range</li>
        <li>Tube format and nominal working volume</li>
        <li>Membrane class and application</li>
        <li>Need for standard versus custom geometry</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class='card'>
      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href='mailto:info@centrivalab.com'>info@centrivalab.com</a></p>
      <p><strong>Company:</strong> Talentground Lda.</p>
      <p><strong>Suggested subject line:</strong> CentrivaLab enquiry – rotor/application</p>
      <p class='small'>Add a form later if needed. For now, a disciplined email route is enough and easier to control.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

  </main>
  
    <footer class='footer'>
      <div class='container footer-grid'>
        <div>
          <h4>CentrivaLab™</h4>
          <p class='small'>Commercial platform based on the Orthogonal Centrifugal Membrane Filter (O-CMF) principle for centrifugal NF/RO membrane screening.</p>
